				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: I do NOT like the new bazaar<a name="73415"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 18 05 1:51 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">Quote:
<br />
------------------------------------------------------------
<br />

<br />
Quote:
<br />
------------------------------------------------------------
<br />
Finding a trader is a joke now. I spent 20 to 30 minutes wandering around
<br />
------------------------------------------------------------
<br />

<br />

<br />
umm ... how about using the Find Trader button in the bazaar search window. I was pleasantly surprised when I noticed that they hadnt broken this feature now that portals are used (kinda worrying that I should expect them to have done, though).
<br />
------------------------------------------------------------
<br />

<br />
Good suggestion. I did try this. However, it just ran me into a wall, leaving me to guess which one of the mazelike tunnels I should take. I took one and ended up inadvertently zoning my trader to Shadowhaven. Of course, in SH weight and agility matter, and my trader couldn't move an inch. I had to gate to POK. Thank goodness I was bound there. In POK I begged--well I donated 200 plat for it--some kindly person to give me a SOW. Since this little gem of an experience, I haven't gone back to the bazaar and I don't intend to if I can help it. Before this huge downgrade to the bazaar, I used to operate a trader whenever I was not playing my main. 
<br />

<br />
Here are a few things that are really bad about the new bazaar:
<br />

<br />
1) Barter zone is coded indoors so you can't selos around. This just wastes time.
<br />

<br />
2) Spreading out the traders and the banks hugely increases the time needed to buy an item and to bank. Another needless waste of time.
<br />

<br />
3) The find trader option didn't work for me. [Since then I have had to download a huge patch since other features--e.g., guild hall--were not working either so this could change]
<br />

<br />
4) The changes to the bazaar weaken the glue (social interaction) that keeps people playing this game. The arena on my server frequently had people of all levels and gear levels interacting together. They chatted and learned things about other classes while horsing around in the arena. It encouraged interaction between top geared level 70 raiders, non-geared level 70s, lower level players, and people just starting to play the game. That just is not happening in any other circumstance in EQ today that I am aware of. Also people who were checking the bazaar or checking their trader would frequently jump down to the lower level to see who was playing in the arena. 
<br />

<br />
Here some suggested changes to the bazaar that would likely improve the situation so players would have some incentive--after years of buying and selling in the bazaar--to once again operate a trader.
<br />

<br />
1) Put all the traders on one level so there is less running around to find a trader.
<br />

<br />
2) Put some signs on the walls with BIG ARROWS telling folks where stuff is. 
<br />

<br />
3) Put the bankers near the traders so people can once again quickly bank and trade.
<br />

<br />
4) Bring back the arena in some form so that people in the bazaar are encouraged to interact with those in the arena.
<br />

<br />
5) Eliminate mazelike tunnels that just cause people to waste valuable game time wandering around.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Drumm
<br />
70 Bard
<br />
</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
DrumofTorv, I think this is your post from Concert hall.  I can't post there, so figured I would post it here.
<br />

<br />
For the find trader button, you should get the mystical stream to follow to the trader, just like using the find command in any other zone.  Not sure why that didn't happen for you, maybe this repatch will have had it.
<br />

<br />
I never used this feature in the old bazaar, so don't know it was working pre-DoN patch, but it worked for me no problem, so that should make the bazaar a little better for me.  
<br />

<br />
However, I do prefer it the old way.
<br />

<br />
Also, regarding tunnels.  I have used the map in this zone to navigate the tunnels, has worked well, so no accidental zoning into SH or wherever.
<br />

<br />
I do agree with another post about the redundency of having the bazaar zone and barter zone.  They should just merge them into 1 zone.
<br />

<br />
As for the arena, I don't care about that<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /></span></td>
