				<td colspan="2"><span>The only things they've really <b>forced</b> us to do is to rely on the golden path &quot;Find Trader&quot; function, and become more reliant on the in-game map (at least for those of us that haven't memorized the floor plan yet).  
<br />

<br />
I'm not really fond of the fact that there are two geographically seperated Trader areas, and that Murphy's Law of eq decrees that if I am going to buy two items, the two relavent traders will be set up in opposite trader areas (sigh).  Overall, though, IMO, it's not as bad as some of you are making it out to be.
<br />

<br />
I will, however, admit that there appears to be more distance to walk (due to floor-plan) and that this is at least a minor time-sink.  It really only adds an extra 5-15 seconds to my bazaar visit, though, so it's no big deal in my mind.
<br />

<br />
Basically, the only two large items I disapprove of is the lack of combining the barter zone with the bazaar zone and also the bicameral Trader areas (that, for sure, should be unicameral).
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
